layers.nm: Based on a review of FY 2026 performance, the business demonstrates a strong and improving financial position, with positive momentum across revenue, profitability, and capital efficiency.  At a high level, monthly revenue has reached $2.4M, reflecting a 12.5% increase versus the prior period, indicating sustained top-line growth. This upward trend is reinforced in the cash flow visualization, where revenue shows steady progression across the months with a notable lift toward the end of the period.  On the cost side, monthly burn rate stands at $320K, down 5.2% from the previous period. This reduction suggests improved expense discipline and operational efficiency, particularly as revenue continues to scale. In the cash flow analysis, expenses remain relatively stable, widening the gap between revenue and costs over time.
